plague-nausea-name = Sea sickness
plague-nausea-desc = The patient vomits, movements slow down, vision becomes blurry.

plague-vomit-name = Black vomit
plague-vomit-desc = The patient retches, their vomit can infect those around them.

plague-blood-vomit-name = Bloody vomit
plague-blood-vomit-desc = The patient vomits blood, harming them and potentially infecting others.

plague-reagent-allergy-name = Rotten blood
plague-reagent-allergy-desc = Infected individuals develop a severe allergy to random reagents. All infected are intolerant to the same reagents.

plague-gastrite-name = Rotting innards
plague-gastrite-desc = Certain foods and drinks poison the patient, causing them harm.

plague-stom-cancer-name = Worm in the belly
plague-stom-cancer-desc = Almost any food now harms the patient, as if something inside is consuming them.

plague-runny-nose-name = Stinky runny nose
plague-runny-nose-desc = The patient constantly sneezes, spreading the infection.

plague-cough-name = Convulsive cough
plague-cough-desc = The patient suffers from a severe cough that can infect those nearby.

plague-blood-cough-name = Bloody wheezing
plague-blood-cough-desc = The patient coughs up blood, causing them damage.

plague-entity-allergy-name = Breath of foulness
plague-entity-allergy-desc = Near certain creatures or objects, the patient begins to suffocate.

plague-asthma-name = Plague breathlessness
plague-asthma-desc = The lungs constrict, preventing a full breath as soon as one starts to run.

plague-lungs-cancer-name = Petrification of the lungs
plague-lungs-cancer-desc = Breathing becomes agonizingly difficult, each breath comes with a wheeze.

plague-itch-name = Itch I
plague-itch-desc = The patient feels a mild but constant itch all over the body.

plague-itch-hard-name = Itch II
plague-itch-hard-desc = The itch becomes unbearable, the patient scratches themselves until they bleed.

plague-weak-skin-name = Weak skin
plague-weak-skin-desc = The skin becomes fragile, any wound deals more damage.

plague-clumsy-name = Plague dance
plague-clumsy-desc = The infected frequently stumbles and falls, losing their balance.

plague-temperature-name = Feverish fire
plague-temperature-desc = The patient is tormented by fever, consciousness becomes confused, all skills become dulled.

plague-skin-cancer-name = Gangrenous plague
plague-skin-cancer-desc = Black gangrene completes its work: itching and flesh rot merge into one, heralding an imminent end.

plague-hiccup-1-name = Hiccup I
plague-hiccup-1-desc = The infected begins to hiccup periodically and sometimes stutters in speech.

plague-hiccup-2-name = Hiccup II
plague-hiccup-2-desc = The infected has a high chance of stuttering and also begins to take damage when hiccupping.

plague-hiccup-3-name = Hiccup III
plague-hiccup-3-desc = Damage from hiccupping is doubled.

plague-pantomime-1-name = Posthumous pantomime I
plague-pantomime-1-desc = The infected begins to swallow some phrases, taking damage in the process.

plague-pantomime-2-name = Posthumous pantomime II
plague-pantomime-2-desc = The infected almost completely loses the ability to speak and takes more damage from a failed attempt.